#### **Day 50: Building the First REST API**
```markdown
# Day 50: Hello World in Spring Boot

**Date:** [Insert Date]

**Topics Covered:**
1. The `@SpringBootApplication` annotation.
2. Creating a REST Controller (`@RestController`).
3. Handling GET Requests (`@GetMapping`).
4. Running the application on Localhost:8080.

**Learning Summary:**
Today I combined everything to build my first web endpoint! I used `@RestController` to define a web layer. I created a simple method that returns a String and mapped it to a URL using `@GetMapping`. When I ran the main class, the embedded Tomcat server started, and I could see my message in the browser.

**Code Snippet:**
```java
package com.example.demo;

import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;
import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestController;

@SpringBootApplication
@RestController
public class Day50Application {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(Day50Application.class, args);
    }

    // Endpoint: http://localhost:8080/hello
    @GetMapping("/hello")
    public String sayHello() {
        return "Hello! I have completed 50 Days of Code!";
    }
}
